   our estate

A journey through the history of an exceptional wine

From the 17th century to the modern day, ten generations of owners have
succeeded each other and left their stamp upon the history of Château
Lascombes. A destiny paved along its way with colourful characters, who all
contributed to the excellence of the wines of Château Lascombes.

   From the oldest known owner, the Chevalier de Lascombes, who bequeathed
   the estate his name, to Alexis Lichine, owner and trader, excellent
   taster and respected by his peers, at the MACSF, which bought Château
   Lascombes.
   Discover the estate

